info.name: NTNU Reflection Tool
info.description:
To get started you will need to have both the backend and the frontend running:

The frontend needs only to be active at the start so that we can get the session cookie for the backend from FEIDE

Steps to get started.

- Start up backend and frontend
- Go into frontend page [http://127.0.0.1:5173/](http://127.0.0.1:5173/)
- Log in
- When login is done, change the url from
    - localhost/auth?code=...
    - to
    - 127.0.0.1:8000/auth?code=...
- If you get an error, remember to empty the cookie berfore.
- When that is done you will need to get the session cookie:
- Right click -> Inspect -> Application -> Cookies
- Copy the session token and go into the [USER](https://go.postman.co/workspace/4935485f-e6d5-45db-8b14-21d225e99973/documentation/24520570-86877364-edc6-495a-88a2-ea01f13ec83b?entity=request-62ede2f4-cd91-4068-90bc-e158b7974005) endpoint
- Click "Headers" -> Update the cookie with new token -> Click send
- If you have two fields with name Cookie, do this
    - Click on "Cookies" that under the send button.
    - Delete (click X) the "127.0.0.1"
    - Now go back and update the cookie
- This will now create a cookie that will affect all the endpoints
- Happy coding!
    

FEIDE documentation:

- Gå til main.py filen
- finn funksjonen:
    - def get_user_data(bearer_token):
- Legg til:
    - print(f"Bearer {bearer_token}")
- Etter det logger du inn på vanlig måte
- Hvis du da sjekker konsollen finner du "token"
- Kopier den og gå til feide endepunktet [HERE](https://go.postman.co/workspace/4935485f-e6d5-45db-8b14-21d225e99973/documentation/24520570-86877364-edc6-495a-88a2-ea01f13ec83b?entity=request-24d76c6e-a67d-4a7a-927f-6c75fbbfc782)
- Oppdater da Athorization Bearer token.
